@page "/pdf-security-tools"

<PageTitle>PDF Security Tools — Lock, Unlock, Redact PDFs Online | PdfToolStack</PageTitle>

<HeadContent>
    <meta name="description"
          content="Secure PDF tools to lock, unlock, redact, sign, and flatten PDF files online. Protect sensitive documents with fast, private PDF workflows." />
    <link rel="canonical" href="https://pdftoolstack.com/pdf-security-tools" />
</HeadContent>

<div class="sechub-page">
    <main class="sechub-container">
        <section class="sechub-hero">
            <div class="sechub-copy">
                <div class="sechub-trust-row">
                    <span>Secure uploads</span>
                    <span>No permanent storage</span>
                    <span>Auto-delete after 1 hour</span>
                </div>
                <h1>PDF security tools for <span class="sechub-gradient-text">sensitive documents</span></h1>
                <p>Lock, unlock, redact, sign, and flatten PDFs before sharing contracts, HR files, invoices, and private business documents.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="sechub-visual" aria-hidden="true">
                <div class="sechub-shield"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M12 3l7 3v5c0 5-3 8-7 10-4-2-7-5-7-10V6z" /><path d="M9 12l2 2 4-5" /></svg></div>
                <div class="sechub-strip sechub-strip-one"></div>
                <div class="sechub-strip sechub-strip-two"></div>
                <div class="sechub-lock"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><rect x="4" y="10" width="16" height="11" rx="2" /><path d="M8 10V7a4 4 0 0 1 8 0v3" /></svg></div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="sechub-section" aria-labelledby="sechub-tools-title">
            <div class="sechub-section-header">
                <span class="sechub-eyebrow">Security workflows</span>
                <h2 id="sechub-tools-title">Protect, clean, and prepare PDFs for sharing</h2>
                <p>Use these working tools for permission-aware document security and sensitive sharing workflows.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="sechub-card-grid">
                <a href="/lock-pdf" class="hub-card" style="--hub-accent:#2563eb;--hub-soft:#eff6ff;"><div class="hub-card-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><rect x="4" y="10" width="16" height="11" rx="2" /><path d="M8 10V7a4 4 0 0 1 8 0v3" /></svg></div><div><span class="hub-card-kicker">Protect</span><h3>Lock PDF</h3><p>Add password protection and supported PDF permissions before sharing.</p></div></a>
                <a href="/unlock-pdf" class="hub-card" style="--hub-accent:#0891b2;--hub-soft:#ecfeff;"><div class="hub-card-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><rect x="4" y="10" width="16" height="11" rx="2" /><path d="M8 10V7a4 4 0 0 1 7.5-2" /></svg></div><div><span class="hub-card-kicker">Authorized</span><h3>Unlock PDF</h3><p>Remove supported protection from PDFs you own or are authorized to modify.</p></div></a>
                <a href="/redact-pdf" class="hub-card" style="--hub-accent:#be123c;--hub-soft:#fff1f2;"><div class="hub-card-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v16a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h12a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V8z" /><path d="M14 2v6h6" /><path d="M7 14h10" /><path d="M7 17h8" /></svg></div><div><span class="hub-card-kicker">Remove</span><h3>Redact PDF</h3><p>Permanently cover sensitive details before a document leaves your team.</p></div></a>
                <a href="/sign-pdf" class="hub-card" style="--hub-accent:#7c3aed;--hub-soft:#f5f3ff;"><div class="hub-card-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M3 17c3-3 4-7 7-7 2 0 3 3 5 3s3-2 6-2" /><path d="M3 21h18" /></svg></div><div><span class="hub-card-kicker">Approve</span><h3>Sign PDF</h3><p>Add an electronic signature to agreements, forms, and approvals.</p></div></a>
                <a href="/flatten-pdf" class="hub-card" style="--hub-accent:#475569;--hub-soft:#f1f5f9;"><div class="hub-card-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M4 5h16" /><path d="M4 12h16" /><path d="M4 19h16" /><path d="M8 3v18" /><path d="M16 3v18" /></svg></div><div><span class="hub-card-kicker">Finalize</span><h3>Flatten PDF</h3><p>Flatten layers and fields into a cleaner final PDF for sharing.</p></div></a>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="sechub-workflow">
            <div><span class="sechub-eyebrow">Related workflow</span><h2>Before a document leaves your organization</h2></div>
            <p>Redact private information, flatten final forms, add signatures where appropriate, then lock the file before sending. Only unlock PDFs you own or are authorized to modify.</p>
            <div class="sechub-workflow-links"><a href="/business-pdf-tools">Business tools</a><a href="/pdf-organizer-tools">Organize first</a><a href="/compress-pdf">Compress before sending</a></div>
        </section>

        <section class="sechub-faq" aria-labelledby="sechub-faq-title">
            <div class="sechub-section-header"><span class="sechub-eyebrow">Questions</span><h2 id="sechub-faq-title">PDF security tools FAQ</h2></div>
            <div class="sechub-faq-grid">
                <article><h3>What PDF security tools are included?</h3><p>Lock PDF, Unlock PDF, Redact PDF, Sign PDF, and Flatten PDF are grouped here.</p></article>
                <article><h3>Can I password-protect a PDF?</h3><p>Yes. Use Lock PDF to add password protection and supported PDF permission controls.</p></article>
                <article><h3>Can I remove a PDF password?</h3><p>Use Unlock PDF only for PDFs you own or are authorized to modify. Password-protected files require the correct password.</p></article>
                <article><h3>Is redaction permanent?</h3><p>Redact PDF is designed to create a finished redacted copy. Always review the download before sharing.</p></article>
                <article><h3>Are electronic signatures legally valid?</h3><p>Electronic signatures may be legally valid depending on jurisdiction and use case. Verify requirements for regulated documents.</p></article>
                <article><h3>Are my files stored?</h3><p>Files are processed securely and deleted within the normal retention window.</p></article>
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>
</div>

